description: The commerce department is planning a long-term solution for exporters' credit issues by considering a credit guarantee fund. This fund will help businesses access finance without needing collaterals. Exporters are currently struggling with declining export credit and high costs. Consulting firm EY is involved in assessing various options for improvement.
title: Govt steps in to address finance concerns of exporters

description: Tragic incidents in Bihar saw eleven youths, including seven from one family, drown while bathing in Rohtas' Sone River and Katihar's floodwaters. In Rohtas, seven children, among them four siblings, lost their lives despite warnings of rising water levels. In Katihar, four youths drowned in floodwaters when their cries went unheard.
title: 7 kids of a Bihar family out for a bath drown in Sone

description: A firm linked to a BJD functionary has been fined Rs 24.2 crore for excess mining at the Kasia hills stone quarry in Odisha's Nayagarh district and must pay by Oct 20. The firm contests these allegations, claiming lack of detailed information from authorities.
title: BJD neta's firm fined Rs 24 crore for 'excess mining'

description: A blaze in Chembur's Siddharth Colony on Sunday claimed the lives of seven family members, including three minors, while two others suffered minor injuries. The fire started at 5am and was reported extinguished by 9:15am. Locals suspect a lit diya and kerosene to be the cause.
title: 7 of family die in Mumbai house blaze

description: Vice-President Jagdeep Dhankhar emphasized that the judiciary and legislature should not engage in executive governance, as it deviates from democratic and constitutional norms. Speaking at an event honoring Karan Singh, Dhankhar highlighted the necessity of maintaining distinct roles for the executive, legislature, and judiciary to preserve democratic integrity.
title: Dhankhar warns against judiciary or legislature exercising executive authority

description: In East Midnapore's Patashpur, a man named Sukhchand Maity was lynched by a mob after being accused of forcing poison on a woman, who later died. The victim's family suspects it was related to her knowledge of Maity's illicit relationship. Both incidents are under separate investigations.
title: Man accused of stripping, killing woman lynched

description: Shaik Jani Basha, known as Jani Master from the Telugu film industry, had his national award for best choreography suspended by the I&B ministry after being arrested for sexual assault under the Pocso Act. He was to be honoured for his work in the song "Megham Karukkatha" from the film Thiruchitrambalam.
title: Jani Master's national award suspended after Pocso case

description: Khyber Pakhtunkhwa chief minister Ali Amin Gandapur went missing after leading a rally in Islamabad, sparking rumors of his arrest. Authorities deny custody and continue searching for him. Meanwhile, protests and violence led to injuries and arrests, including charges against Imran Khan and several PTI members.
title: Pakistan's KP CM still missing from Islamabad; HM denies reports of arrest

description: Calcutta HC, while addressing the case of a nine-year-old's murder and alleged rape in Bengal's Joynagar, emphasized that justice requires a step-by-step process. The court ordered a magistrate-supervised postmortem at a central hospital and included Pocso Act sections in the charges.
title: We don't have a magic wand to deliver instant justice: HC

description: A special council at RG Kar Medical College in Kolkata has sanctioned 59 junior doctors and students for severe misconduct, including physical and mental torture and sexual harassment. With ten expelled and others suspended, names have been forwarded for reevaluation to the West Bengal Medical Council.
title: Doctors, students barred from RG Kar for threats, extortion

description: The Union Cabinet expands India's Classical Languages list to 11, adding Marathi, Pali, Prakrit, Assamese, and Bengali. This move is seen as both a recognition of cultural heritage and a political strategy ahead of state elections, reflecting the ongoing interplay between language and identity politics.
title: What is a Classical Language and how is it chosen?

description: Four people died and over 90 were hospitalized due to fainting and dehydration at a record-breaking IAF airshow in Chennai’s Marina Beach. The event saw around 15 lakh spectators, leading to a chaotic and congested exit. Ambulances were delayed, worsening the situation, and mobile signal jammers obstructed rescue efforts.
title: Four spectators dead in Chennai after IAF air show, many hospitalised

description: Protests in Goa, sparked by Subhash Velingkar's remarks on St Francis Xavier, have eased as police widen their search for him. Velingkar ignored a police notice and applied for anticipatory bail. Authorities are urged to keep religious harmony with peaceful protests ongoing.
title: Goa police expand search for relics row accused, stir subsides

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge criticized PM Modi's economic policies as a 'curse' and accused him of failing the economy. He highlighted a sharp rise in household debt, now at an all-time high of 40% of GDP, and a significant decline in household savings.
title: Modinomics a 'curse', Indian economy in crisis, says Mallikarjun Kharge
2 days after Delhi, Rs 1,800 crore drugs seized in Bhopal

description: CPM MLA KT Jaleel pointed out that a majority of those involved in gold smuggling at Karipur airport are Muslims. He urged religious leaders to condemn such activities as anti-national and stressed that communities should address internal wrongdoings for meaningful reform and progress.
title: Most gold smugglers Muslims, qazi should step in: Kerala MLA

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat, at a gathering in Baran, Rajasthan, urges Hindus to overcome internal divisions based on language, caste, and regional identities for the security of the community. He emphasizes the need for self-initiated action, citing mythological examples and the inclusive nature of Hinduism.
title: Overcome differences for the sake of security, RSS chief tells Hindus

description: With exit polls indicating a hung assembly in Jammu and Kashmir, attention is on the nomination of five members by the lieutenant governor, which could influence the balance of power. The National Conference and Congress challenge this, claiming it undermines democratic principles.
title: 5 nominated MLAs could be key in J&K, LG to name them

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar calls the UN outdated and ineffective, citing its failures in managing global crises like Covid-19 and conflicts in Ukraine and West Asia. He highlights new international groups like the Quad and International Solar Alliance as more effective alternatives.
title: UN a bystander, hasn't kept up with times: EAM S Jaishankar

description: India's National Space Commission has cleared its fifth lunar mission, Lupex, marking a collaboration with Japan's space agency, Jaxa. Aimed at exploring the Moon's resources and developing landing expertise, Lupex follows Chandrayaan-2 and requires cabinet approval. Isro chairman S Somanath indicated this series will build towards future human lunar missions.
title: Go-ahead for 5th Moon mission, Japan to be expedition partner

description: The Indian government is reverting to recruiting railway officers through separate civil and engineering exams, abandoning the unified IRMS system. This change aims to address the need for specialized technical manpower in railways. The newly recruited engineers will fall under various IRMS categories, such as Civil, Mechanical, and Electrical, acknowledging the distinct functional requirements.
title: In U-turn, Railways reverts to pre-Dec 2019 hiring model

description: The Indian Air Force has been practicing shooting high-altitude targets mimicking Chinese spy balloons, with a Rafale jet successfully using an air-to-air missile in the eastern sector. This comes after a Chinese balloon flew over the US in early 2023, prompting contingency preparations.
title: IAF quietly shooting down 'Chinese spy balloons' at high altitudes

description: J&K Congress chief Tariq Hameed Karra and NC president Farooq Abdullah express confidence in winning a majority in the assembly elections. They welcome support from like-minded parties to keep BJP out. PDP hints at joining the NC-Congress coalition in the interest of forming a secular government.
title: After PDP hint, NC-Cong keeps doors open for like-minded parties

description: Fecal coliform levels in the Yamuna river reached a peak of 4,900,000 MPN/100 ml in September, far exceeding the standard limits. Despite improvements in dissolved oxygen and biochemical oxygen demand due to heavy rains, untreated sewage pollution remains severe, particularly at the city's exit points.
title: Why Yamuna is stinking like never before?

description: An explosion near Karachi Airport injured at least four people and caused significant damage. Believed to be caused by a tanker, the blast set vehicles on fire and led to road closures for investigation. Authorities are determining whether it was an accident or deliberate.
title: Massive explosion near Karachi airport leaves several injured

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu announced that Israel's military actions have significantly changed the dynamics since the Hamas attack last year. Praising the army's efforts on the Lebanon border, he affirmed Israel's commitment to defeating enemies in Gaza and Lebanon, and preparing to target Iran. "Together, we will fight, and together we will win -- with God's help," he said.
title: 'We will win': Netanyahu meets troops ahead of Oct 7 attack anniversary

description: Canadian author Jessica Waite reveals in her memoir the shocking double life of her late husband Sean, who had numerous affairs and secret encounters with escorts. After uncovering his deceit, Waite mixed his ashes with dog feces and even consumed some in her despair.
title: 'Took his ashes and ...' :Widow does this after discovering her late husband's affairs

description: India secured a tense six-wicket win over Pakistan in the Women's T20 World Cup, following a heavy defeat to New Zealand. To reach the semifinals, they must triumph against Sri Lanka and Australia, ideally by significant margins. Victory depends on other group matches, with run rates playing a crucial role.
title: Women's T20 WC: Where India stand in race of semifinals

description: Indian skipper Harmanpreet Kaur's 29-run innings helped India win against Pakistan by six wickets in the Women's T20 World Cup. Despite a slow chase of 106, Kaur's efforts kept India's semi-final hopes alive. Key contributions from Shafali Verma, Jemimah Rodrigues, and a disciplined bowling performance were crucial for the victory.
title: T20 WC: India's semi-final chances stay afloat after narrow win vs Pakistan

description: Mayank Yadav secured his first T20I wicket with a powerful 146.1kph delivery, dismissing Bangladesh's Mahmudullah during the opening match at Shrimant Madhavrao Scindia Stadium. The 21-year-old pacer, who gained recognition in IPL 2024, delivered a short ball that Mahmudullah could only edge to deep point. Mayank's return to international cricket demonstrates his impressive pace.
title: Mayank Yadav claims maiden international wicket

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee urges media to halt trials in rape cases, stressing it hampers investigations. She demands the Kultali rape-murder case, involving a 10-year-old, be tried under the POCSO Act, ensuring capital punishment for culprits within three months. Protests erupt in South 24 Parganas, with BJP criticizing women's safety under her administration.
title: Media trials in rape cases hamper probe, should be stopped: CM Mamata

description: Junior doctors in West Bengal, on an indefinite hunger strike, accuse authorities of intimidation and obstructing essential supplies. They demand action on the RG Kar rape and murder case, facing police harassment and negligence. Despite government silence, the doctors remain determined, hoping public support will pressure authorities into addressing their concerns.
title: RG Kar case: Protesting doctors accuse WB govt of 'intimidation tactics'

description: A shooting at Beersheba's central station in southern Israel on Sunday resulted in one death and at least ten injuries. The attack, suspected to be terrorism and executed by a person reportedly associated with Bedouin from the Negev desert, follows a recent Hamas-claimed shooting in Tel Aviv and the ongoing ISrael-Hamas conflict since the October 7 attack last year.
title: Israel shooting: One dead, several hurt in 'suspected terrorist attack'

description: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 has concluded, with Suraj Chavan being crowned the season's ultimate entertainer, securing his rightful place as the winner. Along with the coveted trophy, he also won an EV bike and a Rs 24.60 Lakh prize money. He is a well-known social media influencer and digital content creator celebrated for his relatable and engaging personality, particularly in Marathi content. His journey to fame is characterized by hard work and creativity, inspiring many of his followers.
title: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 winner: All you need to know about Suraj Chavan

description: Young pace sensation Mayank Yadav, becoming only the third Indian seamer after Ajit Agarkar and Arshdeep Singh, bowled a maiden in his debut T20I over against Bangladesh. Mayank's impressive performance continued as he dismissed Mahmudullah an over later for his first international wicket, showcasing his pace and precision, following his attention-grabbing stint in the 2024 IPL.
title: Mayank third Indian to achieve this big feat in T20Is

description: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 Winner Suraj: After impressing fans with their twists and games, Bigg Boss Marathi season 5 winner has been declared. Suraj Chavan, who got popular for his performance in the season, lifted the trophy, while Abhijeet Sawant bagged second position, whereas Nikki Tamboli, Dhananjay Powar and Ankita Walawalkar secured third, fourth and fifth positions respectively.
title: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 winner is Suraj Chavan; takes home trophy

description: Ola CEO Bhavish Aggarwal and comedian Kunal Kamra clashed online over the service quality of Ola's electric scooters. Kamra criticized the company's handling of service centers, while Aggarwal accused Kamra of posting paid tweets and invited him to help solve the issues. The exchange continued with heated remarks from both sides.
title: Ola CEO Bhavish Aggarwal to Kunal Kamra: 'Pay more than you earned..'

description: India secured a commanding seven-wicket victory over Bangladesh in the first T20I match, highlighted by strong bowling performances from debutant Mayank Yadav and returning Varun Chakaravarthy. Key contributions from Sanju Samson, Suryakumar Yadav, and Hardik Pandya ensured a swift chase of Bangladesh's modest total of 127.
title: 1st T20I: Clinical India thrash Bangladesh in series opener

description: A viral Reddit post shows a user claiming he bought an Apple iPhone 16 for just Rs 27,000 by using credit card reward points. The user shared a screenshot indicating Rs 62,930 of the total price was covered by accumulated points on an HDFC Infinia credit card.
title: Reddit user claims to buy iPhone 16 for Rs 27,000 using HDFC Bank card

description: Pakistan is facing turmoil due to widespread PTI protests as it prepares to host the SCO-CHG meeting in Islamabad. Clashes between PTI workers and security forces have led to numerous arrests, including Imran Khan's allies and family members. The government alleges the protests aim to sabotage the summit.
title: Ahead of key SCO meet in Pak, Imran Khan's supporters up the ante

description: India secured a seven-wicket victory over Bangladesh in the first T20I in Gwalior, taking a 1-0 lead in the series. Captain Suryakumar Yadav praised the team's execution and debut performances from Nitish Kumar Reddy and Mayank Yadav, while Arshdeep Singh and Varun Chakravarthy excelled in dismantling Bangladesh's batting lineup.
title: 'We just walked the talk': Suryakumar Yadav
'Will never hurt India's security interests': Maldives prez tells TOI

description: An Indian Air Force air show at Chennai's Marina Beach caused major disruptions and overcrowding, leaving many stranded and resulting in three deaths due to dehydration and other issues. Poor traffic coordination was criticized, and inquiries continue to ascertain the exact causes of the fatalities. Trains were running at increased frequencies to manage the crowd.
title: At least 3 dead in Chennai after IAF air show, many hospitalised

description: Elon Musk's mother, Maye Musk, faced backlash after suggesting people vote with fake names in the US elections, a statement that was widely criticised as promoting voter fraud. Her post, viewed over 2.5 million times, was condemned for being illegal, prompting users to alert the FBI and federal authorities.
title: 'Voter fraud': Netizens alert FBI over tweet by Elon Musk's mother

description: The Leader of Opposition in the Lok Sabha, Rahul Gandhi, accused BJP of inciting communal tensions in Goa, alleging deliberate provocations against Christians and calls for an economic boycott of Muslims. Amid protests following communal remarks by ex-RSS leader Velingkar, CM Sawant promises equal justice, pledging action similar to past incidents. Velingkar remains untraceable.
title: Unrest in Goa: Rahul Gandhi accuses BJP of stoking communal tension

description: A 27-year-old Russian TikTok star, Arina Glazunova, died after falling in a Tbilisi subway underpass while filming a video. She tripped on a knee-high wall, resulting in fatal injuries. Locals criticized the lack of safety measures. Tbilisi’s City Hall stated the structure met Soviet-era standards. The incident has sparked widespread reactions on social media.
title: Watch: TikTok star's last moments captured on camera

description: Indian bowler Renuka Singh delivered a sensational inswinger to dismiss Pakistan’s opener Gull Feroza for a duck, providing a crucial early breakthrough in the Women's T20 World Cup match in Dubai. Pakistan captain Fatima Sana won the toss and elected to bat, while both teams made tactical changes to their playing XIs.
title: Absolute jaffa! Renuka knocks over Gull with a perfect inswinger. Watch

description: India's External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar emphasized the nation's need to stay connected with major powers amidst Middle East and Russia-Ukraine conflicts. He highlighted India's role in diplomatic communication and support from the Global South, while noting PM Modi's active engagement with leaders to foster peace.
title: PM Modi one of few world leaders who can talk to Kyiv & Moscow: Jaishankar

description: Rishabh Pant's unbeaten 89* at the Gabba in January 2021 led India to a historic Test win against Australia. Despite numerous injuries, India chased down 328 runs. Pant's aggressive yet composed batting, especially during the final session, sealed a series win and marked a significant milestone for Indian cricket.
title: Pant's Masterclass: How India conquered the fortress Gabba

description: Ahead of the 2025 IPL season, AB de Villiers mentions that it would be a sensational move if Rohit Sharma switched from Mumbai Indians to Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Despite recent struggles and controversies within MI, De Villiers deems this switch highly improbable, giving it a near impossibility.
title: 'If Rohit Sharma moves to RCB...': ABD dwells on the 'big move' in IPL

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar highlighted the need for the United Nations to evolve as it struggles to address major global issues, pushing countries to seek alternatives. Speaking at the Kautilya Economic Conclave, he noted the UN's limited role in crises like COVID-19 and conflicts in Europe and the Middle East, emphasizing the rising ‘non-UN space’ in global politics.
title: 'Like an old company ...': Jaishankar's scathing criticism of UN

description: Military drones have transformed global conflicts, significantly altering battlefield dynamics in wars from Nagorno-Karabakh to Ukraine. Countries like the US, Turkey, and Poland lead in drone capabilities, utilizing them for surveillance, strikes, and signal jamming. Global powers continuously invest in drone technology to maintain their edge in modern warfare, enhancing military presence and influence.
title: Top 10 countries with most military drones in the world

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar humorously dodged a choice between dining with Kim Jong Un or George Soros, citing Navratri fasting. Known for quick-witted responses, Jaishankar previously addressed India's evolving relationship with the US and defended Prime Minister Modi against critics like Soros, whom he called a 'dangerous' outsider. He will visit Pakistan for the SCO meeting on October 15-16.
title: Dinner with Kim Jong Un or George Soros? Jaishankar's reply goes viral
Maldives prez Muizzu in India for first State visit, to meet PM Modi on Oct 7

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticized BJP's governance during the 'Janta Ki Adalat' at Chhatrasal Stadium, challenging PM Modi to provide free electricity in NDA-ruled states before Delhi polls. He accused BJP of causing inflation, corruption, and unemployment, and vowed to secure full statehood for Delhi, condemning the LG's control and recounting personal hardships faced.
title: 'I will campaign for BJP if ...': What Kejriwal said at Janta Ki Adalat rally

description: Aam Aadmi Party leader Mandeep Singh Brar was injured in a shooting in Punjab's Fazilka district after an altercation with Shiromani Akali Dal workers. AAP MLA Jagdeep Kamboj accused Akali Dal leader Vardev Singh Noni Mann of firing at Brar. Brar, who is running for sarpanch, is now stable, and police promise strict action.
title: Punjab AAP leader shot at during argument with Akali Dal leader

description: Authorities seized drugs and raw materials worth Rs 1,814 crore from a Bhopal factory in a joint raid by Gujarat ATS and NCB, indicating a significant achievement in the battle against drug trafficking. Minister Harsh Sanghavi praised the agencies and called for public support.
title: Drugs, raw material worth Rs 1,814 crore seized from Bhopal factory

description: A viral video shows a thief snatching a young girl's mobile phone through a train window at night. The footage has raised concerns about increasing mobile robberies and safety on public transport. The clip captures the girl’s futile efforts to save her phone, sparking outrage and discussions on social media.
title: Watch: Thief snatches phone from little girl's hand through train window
Bengaluru cop stops Lamborghini for inspection, requests for selfie

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat emphasized the unity of Hindu society in India, urging the elimination of differences in language, caste, and regional disputes to ensure security. He highlighted the importance of discipline, duty towards the state, and social harmony. The event in Rajasthan was attended by 3,827 volunteers and senior RSS leaders.
title: RSS chief calls for 'unity' among Hindus, 'eliminate' caste differences

description: Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson returned to WWE at Bad Blood 2024. He reignited his feud with Cody Rhodes while acknowledging his father, Dusty Rhodes. Backstage, The Rock praised Dusty but stated his disdain for Cody. The Rock's future in WWE is still uncertain, generating excitement among fans.
title: Rock's message for Cody Rhodes after WWE Bad Blood went off air

description: Mossad's covert operation tricked Hezbollah into using booby-trapped AR924 pagers, leading to explosions that killed or injured around 3,000 members on September 17. Concealed as secure communication devices, the pagers significantly disrupted Hezbollah's communications and inflicted severe casualties, highlighting the ingenuity of modern spycraft.
title: How Israel's Mossad convinced Hezbollah to buy its exploding pagers

description: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar has strengthened ties with ally BJP during his party's state executive committee meeting. He praised PM Narendra Modi, Union minister Amit Shah, and BJP president JP Nadda for the financial help in the Union Budget. Nitish encouraged the Centre to provide more financial assistance and highlighted the increase in Bihar's annual budget under his tenure.
title: Eye on Bihar polls, Nitish attempts to boost ties with BJP

description: A senior BJP leader in Pauri Garhwal, Uttarakhand, faces charges for incitement and religious insult after allegedly threatening to burn down shops of the minority community and harm them due to incidents involving 'love jihad.' The police have taken legal action, citing directives on derogatory speeches.
title: BJP neta threatens to burn down Muslims’ shops over ‘love jihad’ in Uttarakhand
